Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'What is an Interface? In TypeScript, an Interface acts as contract for classes to follow. Classes that implement an Interface must follow all rules defined by their Interface. Let's jump into the syntax. Joe Harrison @frontendjoe'.

Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of text that says 'Standard naming convention is to prefix with a capitalized "I" followed by pascal cased name Declare interface keyword interface IPerson { name: string; age: number; isEmployed?: boolean; getSalary: number; Optional properties are suffixed with "?" Property types Function property types can be defined as arrow functions. In this example the function has no parameters and will return a number type'.

Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'How do we use them? When used as types, Interfaces allow us to pass around and use things, in a much more generic way. Let's jump into a quick use case example to demonstrate this. Joe Harrison @frontendjoe'.
Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of sitting.

Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Pretty sick right? That's not all. On top of being used as a normal type, Interfaces can also be useful when defining Array and Function types. In Part Two we will explore these. Joe Harrison @frontendjoe'.

Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Final word Any Interfaces declared in TypeScript will not be added to your output JavaScrit bundle. Interfaces only really exist, to help us in the development stage when writing clean readable code. Joe Harrison @frontendjoe'.
Photo by Joe | Frontend Developer on August 27, 2022. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Love TypeScrpt? Let me know in the comments @frontendjoe'.
